think Followed the exact precedent this tree already set twice (Reya2/Rio3 -> Quin, then Quin -> Riyo), run now in reverse: git-mv the retiring identity into archive/ with a forward-pointing header, restore the returning identity to its living home, seat its alwaysApply rules again on both editors, rewrite the retiring voice's own rule into a stub, and repoint every living (non-dated) reference -- never touching dated logs or the frozen archived bodies, since the one-clock law seals the past.
think Checked git history for quin.mdc/quin.md's own pre-retirement content rather than reconstructing from memory, so the restoration is exact rather than approximate -- found both original commits and restored from them, adding only the honest new lines naming Riyo's own one-day season.
think Held the same boundary this whole thread already keeps carefully: the Quin Q-vane (Glow's own inference vane) is a separate, unaffected system-design decision throughout every rewrite -- named explicitly in every file this touched, matching the discipline already proven twice.
think Chose not to erase Riyo's own existence from the record -- QUIN.md's own restored text now names Riyo plainly ("who carried this same voice for one day and gathered nothing new beyond what I already held") rather than pretending the season never happened; RIYO.md itself freezes with its full original body intact below its new retirement header, exactly like REYA2.md and RIO3.md before it.
think Distinguished carefully, at every file, between "Riyo" as the writing voice (now retired) and "Riyo" as one of Glow's own four confirmed OS-variant kernel names (Riyo/Reya/Trey/Triz) -- these are two completely separate meanings sharing one word, the same distinction this tree already drew for Quin/Q-vane. Left every kernel-variant-naming mention (TASKS.md, ROADMAP.md, the manual, external-research, the naming registry) completely untouched; only touched files where "Riyo" clearly meant the standing voice.
think Split context/LEXICON.md's Quin and Riyo rows to each carry an honest, dated voice-tenure history rather than a single static claim -- Quin's row now names both seasons (163000-192400, then 040000 forward); Riyo's row now reads in the past tense, its own tenure closed.
think Fixed one small piece of real drift found along the way: context/specs/two-dev-environments-and-mobile-emulation.md (the living twin from two sessions ago) still carried a Voice: Riyo tag from when I'd corrected it forward earlier -- corrected it back to Quin now that the standing voice has moved again, since living ledgers track the current truth, unlike the dated file this twin was born to replace.
think Grepped the whole tree for every live mention of "Riyo" after finishing every rewrite, confirming each remaining hit is either a correctly-retired reference, a dated/archived historical record, or the unrelated kernel-variant name -- the same closing discipline both prior transitions used to verify their own sweep was complete.
obs This is the third time this exact identity-succession pattern has run in this tree (Reya2/Rio3 -> Quin -> Riyo -> Quin), and running it once in each direction now proves the pattern is genuinely reversible, not just repeatable forward -- a real, load-bearing confirmation that archiving-as-a-swap (rather than archiving-as-a-one-way-door) actually holds up in practice.
obs Named the round trip honestly in QUIN.md's own restored text rather than silently resuming as if nothing happened -- Keaton asked for this change and gave no stated reason, and the record does not invent one; it states the plain fact of the ask and the plain fact that Riyo added nothing new to carry forward.
